Deputy National Security Advisor Antony Blinken met with Sigrid Kaag, the Special Coordinator of the United Nations-Organization for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) Joint Mission in Syria. They discussed the progress of the Joint Mission in eliminating Syria's chemical weapons program and expressed strong U.S. support for its work. The conversation focused on ensuring that the Syrian government continues its efforts to remove chemical weapons and meet the June 30 deadline for destruction. Deputy NSA Blinken thanked Special Coordinator Kaag for her leadership and the dedication of her staff.